            "id": "4767126",
            "title": "LRT Capital Management February 2025 Investor Update",
            "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2172124417/image_2172124417.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Update progress concept. Software upgrade icon on virtual screen\" data-id=\"2172124417\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"662px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2172124417/image_2172124417.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2172124417/image_2172124417.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2172124417/image_2172124417.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2172124417/image_2172124417.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2172124417/image_2172124417.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2172124417/image_2172124417.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2172124417/image_2172124417.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2172124417/image_2172124417.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">Funtap/iStock via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div></p> <h2>Dear Friends &amp; Partners,</h2> <p>Our investment returns are summarized in the table below:</p> <span class=\"table-responsive\"><span class=\"table-scroll-wrapper\"><span data-intersection-boundary=\"start\"></span><table> <tr class=\"bg-b\"> <td><p><strong>Strategy</strong></p></td> <td><p><strong>Month</strong></p></td> <td><p><strong>YTD</strong></p></td> <td><p><strong>12 Months</strong></p></td> <td><p><strong>24 Months</strong></p></td> <td><p><strong>36 Months</strong></p></td> <td><p><strong>Inception</strong></p></td> </tr> <tr> <td><p>LRT Global Opportunities</p></td> <td><p>-9.97%</p></td> <td><p>-3.21%</p></td> <td><p>-4.66%</p></td> <td><p>+9.57%</p></td> <td><p>+3.26%</p></td> <td><p>+18.46%</p></td> </tr> </table>\n<span data-intersection-boundary=\"end\"></span></span><button class=\"table-enlarge-button\"><svg viewbox=\"0 0 16 16\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"table-enlarge-icon\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16 11a5 5 0 0 1-5 5H5a5 5 0 0 1-5-5V5a5 5 0 0 1 5-5h6a5 5 0 0 1 5 5v6zm-4.5-2.5h2v-6h-6v2h4v4zm-9-1h2v4h4v2h-6v-6z\"></path></svg>Click to enlarge</button></span> <p><em>Results as of 2/28/2024. Periods longer than one year are annualized. All results are net of all fees and expenses. Past returns are no guarantee of future results. Please see the end of this letter for additional disclosures.</em></p> <p>LRT Global Opportunities is a <strong>systematic</strong> long/short strategy that seeks to generate positive returns while <strong>controlling downside risks</strong> and maintaining a low net exposure to the equity markets.</p> <p>For February, the strategy returned -9.97%, bringing the year-to-date performance to -3.21%, net of fees. Beta-adjusted net exposure stood at 37.38% at month-end. Our long positions declined significantly, though partially offset by gains in our short positions. Please refer to the appendix for additional disclosures.</p> <p>February was a challenging month, with weaker-than-expected performance, driven largely by earnings disappointments in several long positions. The Trade Desk, Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TTD\" title=\"The Trade Desk, Inc.\">TTD</a>), Cognex Corporation (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CGNX\" title=\"Cognex Corporation\">CGNX</a>), and TriNet Group, Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TNET\" title=\"TriNet Group, Inc.\">TNET</a>) all declined sharply following earnings reports that fell short of expectations. Interestingly, even companies that exceeded earnings estimates, such as Comfort Systems USA Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FIX\" title=\"Comfort Systems USA, Inc.\">FIX</a>) and Integrated Electrical Services, Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IESC\" title=\"IES Holdings, Inc.\">IESC</a>), saw sharp declines-highlighting broader market fragility. Additionally, UnitedHealth Group Incorporated (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/UNH\" title=\"UnitedHealth Group Incorporated\">UNH</a>) faced significant selling pressure after reports surfaced in the Wall Street Journal regarding an investigation into its Medicare Advantage billing practices. In short, February was a month of unfortunate events across multiple holdings.</p> <p>We have seen a modest rebound in early March and believe the current environment is presenting compelling opportunities in high-quality companies. Businesses such as TriNet Group, Inc., Brown-Forman Corporation (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BF.B\" title=\"Brown-Forman Corporation\">BF.B</a>), TFI International Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TFII\" title=\"TFI International Inc.\">TFII</a>), and UnitedHealth Group Incorporated offer meaningful upside potential. Market concerns over tariffs and the potential for a U.S. economic slowdown are valid, but we believe that our portfolio companies-those with strong business models and resilient balance sheets-are well-positioned to navigate these uncertainties and outperform over time.</p> <p>I deeply appreciate the trust you place in me as a steward of your capital. As always, please feel free to reach out with any questions. Your continued support is greatly valued.</p> <span class=\"table-responsive\"><span class=\"table-scroll-wrapper\"><span data-intersection-boundary=\"start\"></span><table><tr><td> <p><str